  <description type="morphology">Stems often tangled among themselves, 3–20 dm. Leaves: petiole 3–25 mm; blade
        ovate, triangular, or rhombic-orbiculate, 15–60 × 10–45 mm, base obtuse, truncate, or
        cordate, margins shallowly sinuate, apex usually acute or acuminate, sometimes obtuse or
        round. Inflorescences: peduncle 4–6 cm; umbel 4–11-flowered; pedicel 3–15 mm. Perianths pale
        greenish yellow, 3–4 mm, glabrous or with few minute hairs externally near margin of limb.
        Fruits usually reflexed at tip of pedicel, 7–10 × 1.5–2 mm.</description>
